ActDepartment of Citizenship and Immigration Act
SubjectAgreement with respect to the Atlantic Immigration Program
PrecisOrder authorizing the Minister of Citizenship and Immigration, to ENTER INTO the following four AGREEMENTS with the Governments of NOVA SCOTIA, NEW BRUNSWICK, PRINCE EDWARD ISLAND, and NEWFOUNDLAND AND LABRADOR (the Atlantic Provinces), respectively: (1) the Canada-Nova Scotia Agreement on the Atlantic Immigration Program; (2) the Canada-New Brunswick Agreement on the Atlantic Immigration Program; (3) the Canada-Prince Edward Island Agreement on the Atlantic Immigration Program, and (4) the Canada-Newfoundland and Labrador Agreement on the Atlantic Immigration Program. The Agreements will come into force on January 1, 2022, or upon the date the Agreements are signed by both parties, whichever is later, and remain in place indefinitely.
